questions.question:
Given the following on a healthcare warehouse:

GRANT SELECT ON dbo.Patients TO Receptionist;
DENY SELECT ON dbo.Patients(MedicalHistory) TO Receptionist;

A user in the Receptionist role runs: SELECT Name, MedicalHistory FROM dbo.Patients; What is the result?

A warehouse uses this pattern for an ETL service account:

GRANT EXECUTE ON dbo.usp_LoadSales TO [etl@contoso.com];
DENY SELECT ON dbo.Sales TO [etl@contoso.com];

The procedure usp_LoadSales reads and writes dbo.Sales internally. What can etl@contoso.com do?
